Human rights campaigners object to a TV programme showing imprisoned Sakineh Mohammadi Ashtiani returning home. (The Guardian)A man is sentenced to death in Egypt for killing Copts at a Christmas mass a year ago. (CNN) (Xinhua)The United States Treasury Department says "no" to calls by enraged American politicians to have Julian Assange and the WikiLeaks website added to its economic blacklist or sanctions list like so-called "terrorist groups". The Treasury Department cites a lack of "evidence at this time". (CBS News)